[2] Thuringia: dairy farm, tuberculosis (untyped), investigation, EC presentation
Date: Mon 24 Oct 2022
Source: EC Animal Health and Welfare - SCoPAFF meeting, 21 Oct 2022, Germany's PowerPoint presentation [abridged, edited]
https://food.ec.europa.eu/system/files/2022-10/reg-com_ahw_20221021_mtbc-cattle_deu.pdf


Infection with _Mycobacterium tuberculosis_ complex of bovine in Germany (4 slides)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Slide 1.

MTBC in cattle - dairy production in Thuringia:

After suspicion during slaughter, sampling and testing was performed.
Notification on 13 Oct 2022
- 3245 bovines
- 1300 milking cows
- 3 different epidemiological units, some km apart

[A map, indicating the outbreak's location, is included in slide 1.]

Slide 2.

MTBC in cattle - measures as of DelReg2020/689 Art. 20 and 24: [see comment]

1. Withdrawal of disease-free status
2. Movement restrictions
3. Safe disposal of positive animals and milk
4. Tuberculin skin tests ongoing: so far 3 positive, 3 not negative, all euthanised
5. Epidemiological enquiry

Slide 3.

MTBC in cattle - epidemiological results:

1. Movements within the last 5 years
2. 1/2 was slaughtered
3. Member States
4. Third countries
5. national

Slide 4.

